==English==

===Etymology===
1920s. A pun on ''the business''.

===Noun phrase===
'''the [[bee]]’s [[knee]]s'''

#{{idiom}} Something [[excellent]], [[outstanding]].
#:''We had strawberry shortcake for breakfast on Saturday and the kids thought it was '''the bee's knees'''.''

